# **Frontend Developer Technical Assignment**

## **AI Chat Application with Nested Comments System**

Build a complete AI chat interface using Next.js with server-side rendering, autocomplete search, and nested comment functionality. This assignment evaluates your frontend architecture skills, SSR/CSR understanding, and complex UI implementations.

â€‹

---

## **Technology Stack**

Required Technologies:

* Next.js 14+ (App Router)  
* TanStack Query for caching  
* TypeScript (preferred)  
* React Server Components & Client Components  
* Use the shad cn components 

---

## **Core Features**

## **1\. Next.js Architecture Implementation**

* App Router Structure \- Proper file-based routing with Next.js App Router  
* Server Components \- Use for static content like initial questions and responses  
* Client Components \- Use for interactive elements like search and comments  
* SSR/CSR Hybrid \- Questions list should be server-rendered, comments client-rendered  
* Hydration Handling \- Smooth transition from server-rendered to interactive content

## **2\. Scalable Autocomplete Search**

* Server-Side Search \- Initial search results should come from server  
* Client-Side Caching \- Use TanStack Query for caching subsequent searches  
* Character Highlighting \- Bold/highlight matching text in dropdown results  
  ![][image1]  
* Keyboard Navigation \- Support arrow keys, Enter, and Escape key handling  
* Debounced Input \- Optimize performance with proper input debouncing

## **3\. Chat Response System**

* Server-Rendered Questions \- Pre-load 1000+ questions on server side **( Use the Placeholder apis for data )**  
* Hardcoded Responses \- Each question should have a predefined answer  
* Dynamic Rendering \- Selected questions appear as chat messages  
* Performance Optimization \- Implement code splitting for better loading  
  ![][image2]

## **4\. Nested Comment System**

* Multi-level Threading \- Support minimum 4 levels of comment nesting  
* CRUD Operations \- Users can create, edit, and delete comments  
* Optimistic Updates \- UI should update immediately with rollback on errors  
* Vote System \- Upvote/downvote functionality with data persistence  
* Real-time Sorting \- Sort comments by newest, oldest, or most voted  
  ![][image3]

## **Chat Interface**

* Question submission \- Selected question appears as user message in chat  
* Sticky headings \- Current question in viewport becomes floating header at top  
* Scroll behavior \- Header changes as user scrolls through different questions  
* Clean layout \- Professional chat UI like ChatGPT/Perplexity  
  ![][image4]

---

## **Technical Implementation Requirements**

## **Server vs Client Components ( Optional )**

Server Components (SSR):

* Initial questions list rendering  
* Static response content display  
* SEO-optimized content structure  
* Initial data loading

Client Components (CSR):

* Search autocomplete functionality  
* Comment interactions (add, edit, delete, vote)  
* Real-time UI updates and animations  
* User interaction handling

## **DOM Manipulation Requirements**

Direct DOM Operations:

* Focus management in search dropdown  
* Scroll behavior for new comments  
* Dynamic height calculations for comment threads  
* Efficient event handling for nested elements

Performance Optimizations:

* Virtual scrolling for large comment lists  
* Intersection Observer for lazy loading  
* Proper event listener cleanup  
* Memory leak prevention

## **SSR/CSR Hybrid Implementation**

Server-Side Rendering:

* Questions and responses should be pre-rendered on server  
* SEO-friendly content structure  
* Fast initial page load  
* Progressive enhancement approach

Client-Side Interactions:

* Interactive search with real-time filtering  
* Comment system with immediate feedback  
* Smooth animations and transitions  
* Local state management for user interactions

Hydration Strategies:

* App should work without JavaScript (progressive enhancement)  
* Only interactive components should hydrate on client  
* Implement proper error boundaries  
* Handle hydration mismatches gracefully
